SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 197
BY SENATOR ABRAHAM
A RESOLUTION
To express the sincere and heartfelt condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of
Louisiana upon the passing of Carroll Wade Shaddock Jr.
WHEREAS, it is with great regret that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana has
learned of the passing of Carroll Wade Shaddock Jr. (Wade), a beloved husband, father,
brother, grandfather, great-grandfather, and respected leader, on November 27, 2025, at the
age of ninety-two; and
WHEREAS, Wade's life was dedicated to public service, integrity, and an
unwavering commitment to helping others; and
WHEREAS, he attended Lake Charles city schools and in May of 1952, enlisted in
the United States Army, later graduating from the United States Military Academy at West
Point in New York in 1957; and
WHEREAS, upon graduating from West Point, Wade was commissioned as a Second
Lieutenant in the Army where he became an army ranger and a paratrooper; and
WHEREAS, he served two one-year tours in Vietnam, and other short tours in
Alaska, Puerto Rico, and Greenland; and
WHEREAS, Wade's final career, completed at age eighty-nine, was at the H.C. Drew
Estate, a nonprofit organization that provides educational grants to public and private
schools for college scholarships and to various other educational and nonprofit organizations
in Southwest Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, he was a sports lover and found great joy in cheering on McNeese,
LSU, KU, and West Point, and Wade and his wife, Missy, personally originated numerous
scholarships at McNeese State University and SOWELA Technical Community College; and
WHEREAS, Wade was a devoted public servant who believed that true leadership
meant showing up for the community every single day, and exemplified that belief through
service, including mentoring young men in the community and guiding over two hundred
people through a West Point football weekend so that they might better appreciate and learn
the values and contributions of the United States Military Academy; and
