WHEREAS, Wade and Missy worked diligently to strengthen their familial bonds
by hosting holiday celebrations that not only kept old traditions alive but created cherished
new ones; and
WHEREAS, Wade was a leader, trusted friend, and pillar of the community, where
he was known for his kind heart and generous spirit, creating a lasting impact for generations
to come; and
WHEREAS, he is survived by his wife of sixty-six years, Mary Ruth (Missy); two
daughters, Cindy Hanks (Ricky) and Becky Clements (Brian); five grandchildren, Erin-Beth
Carter (Garret), Meghan Abraham (Ross), Taylor Clements (Camryn), Ben Clements
(Katie), and Ellie Santoro (Joey); ten great-grandchildren; and siblings, Julia Goeller and
Tom Shaddock; and
WHEREAS, Wade lived his life with dignity and humility, always placing family,
faith, and service above all else and his legacy will live on in the countless lives he touched
with his wisdom and kindness, as well as in the strong and vibrant community he helped
build.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby express sincere and heartfelt condolences to the family of Carroll Wade
Shaddock Jr., upon his passing and does hereby commend his dedication to his community
and his many accomplishments.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
family of Carroll Wade Shaddock Jr.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
